---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: "How much investment do I need?",
    a: "We recommend you have £500 to start. You will need to buy a printer, labels, boxes and your stock from this amount. However, the more capital you invest, the more products you can source, and the more sales you'll make.",
  },
  {
    q: "How is this different to the Kickstarter Academy?",
    a: "The Kickstarter Academy is where we began teaching Amazon FBA. It's packed with unlimited one-on-one sessions over Zoom with our experts and intensive support. While it's been a powerful launchpad for producing 6-Figure sellers, it was a privilege for financially blessed people with a professional background who could comfortably afford to invest at least £5k — which not everyone can. The Amazon FBA Bootcamp on the other hand is a budget-friendly workshop designed to give more people the opportunity to dive into Amazon FBA and have a real shot at building their own 6-Figure FBA Business. It may not be on the same level as the Kickstarter Academy — but it offers you the most affordable way to be coached by me and my expert team.",
  },
  {
    q: "Can I get a refund if I miss it or change my mind?",
    a: "Sadly, since this is a live programme, we cannot issue refunds. You can however transfer your place to somebody else if for some reason you cannot attend. Email techsupport@makeymoney.co.uk for further support.",
  },
  {
    q: "Will this event be running again?",
    a: "This event might not happen again as it is a case-study programme to see if it can fulfil the desired purpose of providing affordable FBA Coaching. So we recommend you attend this bootcamp and make the best of it — you'll walk away with knowledge that'll open the door to starting your own profitable FBA Business.",
  },
  {
    q: "Will I need to use Alibaba?",
    a: "We're not going anywhere near risky Chinese suppliers — we'll use UK-based suppliers only. This training teaches the wholesale and arbitrage model, not private labelling, importing from abroad, or starting your own brand.",
  },
  {
    q: "What if I need more support after the bootcamp?",
    a: "You didn't think we'd just school you and let you figure the rest out on your own, did you? That's exactly why we include 90 days post-bootcamp aftercare support which includes: 1) 5 hours of intensive face-to-face Amazon FBA Strategy training. 2) A custom digital course packed with training videos, resources, and hand-holding advice, with lifetime access. 3) 90 days access to our private support group for 24/7 support. 4) 90 days worth of live group coaching calls covering leadership, business development, habit building, cost management, sourcing, and scaling. (These take place twice a week and are recorded and placed into your portal in case you miss them.)",
  },
  {
    q: "When and where is the event taking place?",
    a: "The event is being held at London Chigwell Prince Regent Hotel, Manor Rd, Chigwell, Essex IG8 8AE. We have a swanky private room and lunch is included. You have the option to choose EITHER Saturday 2nd March 9.30–3.00pm or Sunday 3rd March 9.30–3.00pm. We are ALSO holding a business networking event on the evening of 2nd March at the same venue — so you're VERY likely to attend that too!",
  },
  {
    q: "How much money will I earn?",
    a: "That's not something we can answer or predict — and honestly? Any coach that promises you a certain figure is pulling your leg! How much you earn depends entirely on how much effort, time and money you put into your business. You might make a few hundred, thousands, or even a million. It's 100% down to you.",
  },
  {
    q: "What if I'm a beginner or already sell on Amazon?",
    a: "The purpose of this Bootcamp is to provide guidance and support to complete newbies who've never sold or even heard of Amazon FBA before — regardless of their education level or technical skills.",
  },
  {
    q: "I have more questions.",
    a: "Sure! If you have any questions related to the Bootcamp Training, email them to info@makeymoney.co.uk",
  },
];
---

<section class="faq" id="faq">
  <div class="faq-inner">
    <div class="faq-header">
      <h2 class="display-headline faq-headline reveal">
        Frequently Asked<br /><em>Questions.</em>
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-list">
      {faqs.map((item, i) => (
        <div class="faq-item reveal" style={`transition-delay: ${(i % 4) * 0.06}s`} data-faq>
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
            <span class="faq-q-num">{String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}</span>
            <span class="faq-q-text">{item.q}</span>
            <span class="faq-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i></span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p class="faq-answer-text">{item.a}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="faq-still reveal">
      <div class="faq-still-rule"></div>
      <p class="faq-still-heading">Still have questions?</p>
      <p class="faq-still-sub">We're happy to help — reach out and we'll get back to you.</p>
      <a href="mailto:info@makeymoney.co.uk" class="faq-still-link">Email us directly</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq {
    background: var(--color-off-white);
    padding: 130px 0 110px;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .faq::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, rgba(26,26,26,0.15), transparent);
  }

  .faq-inner {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 60px;
    position: relative;
  }

  .faq-header {
    margin-bottom: 72px;
  }

  .faq-headline {
    font-size: clamp(30px, 4vw, 56px);
    color: var(--color-near-black);
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .faq-headline em {
    color: var(--color-amazon);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* List */
  .faq-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.1);
  }

  .faq-item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.1);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .faq-question {
    width: 100%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 20px;
    padding: 28px 0;
    background: none;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    text-align: left;
    transition: background 0.2s ease;
  }

  .faq-question:hover .faq-q-text {
    color: var(--color-near-black);
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .faq-q-num {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--color-gold);
    opacity: 0.7;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 28px;
  }

  .faq-q-text {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(16px, 2vw, 19px);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-near-black);
    opacity: 0.85;
    flex: 1;
    line-height: 1.4;
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
  }

  .faq-icon {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--color-gold);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    transition: transform 0.35s ease;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .faq-item.open .faq-icon {
    transform: rotate(45deg);
  }

  /* Answer */
  .faq-answer {
    max-height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: max-height 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
  }

  .faq-item.open .faq-answer {
    max-height: 800px;
  }

  .faq-answer-text {
    font-family: 'Lora', serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #666;
    padding: 0 0 28px 48px;
  }

  /* Still question */
  .faq-still {
    margin-top: 80px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: center;
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .faq-still-rule {
    width: 48px;
    height: 2px;
    background: var(--color-gold);
    opacity: 0.6;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .faq-still-heading {
    font-family: 'Lora', serif;
    font-size: clamp(26px, 3vw, 38px);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-near-black);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .faq-still-sub {
    font-family: 'Lora', serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--color-near-black);
    opacity: 0.5;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .faq-still-link {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #0e0703;
    background: var(--color-gold);
    padding: 14px 32px;
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-top: 8px;
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
  }

  .faq-still-link:hover {
    opacity: 0.85;
  }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .faq { padding: 72px 0 64px; }
    .faq-inner { padding: 0 24px; }
    .faq-answer-text { padding-left: 0; }
    .faq-header { margin-bottom: 48px; }
    .faq-q-num { display: none; }
  }
</style>

<script>
  // Accordion logic
  document.querySelectorAll('[data-faq]').forEach((item) => {
    const btn = item.querySelector('.faq-question');
    btn?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const isOpen = item.classList.contains('open');
      // Close all
      document.querySelectorAll('[data-faq].open').forEach((other) => {
        other.classList.remove('open');
        other.querySelector('.faq-question')?.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
      });
      // Toggle current
      if (!isOpen) {
        item.classList.add('open');
        btn.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');
      }
    });
  });
</script>
